.TH "rio_route_clr_table" 9 "rio_route_clr_table" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rio_route_clr_table \- Clear a switch routing table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rio_route_clr_table
.BI "(struct rio_dev *rdev "  ","
.BI "u16 table "  ","
.BI "int lock "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
RIO device
.IP "table" 12
Routing table ID
.IP "lock" 12
apply a hardware lock on switch device flag (1=lock, 0=no_lock)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If available calls the switch specific \fBclr_table\fP method to clear a switch
routing table. Otherwise uses standard RT write method as defined by RapidIO
specification. A specific routing table can be selected using the \fItable\fP
argument if a switch has per port routing tables or the standard (or global)
table may be used by passing RIO_GLOBAL_TABLE in \fItable\fP.

Returns 0 on success or -EINVAL on failure.
